node.text: Collaborated with @Qualcomm for this Mobile Photography Tutorial! Shot on the #Snapdragon 888 5G Mobile Platform! Check out @SnapdragonInsiders for more pro-quality #ShotOnSnapdragon photos [ad]

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Washington. May be an image of nature and mountain.

node.text: Washington trying to do it’s best impersonation of New Zealand lakes + waterfalls 🤠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Oregon with @michelle.lawrencee. May be an image of bird, nature and lake.

node.text: Volcanic sunrises are 🌋 Even in the summer this place can get chilly enough in the morning where there’s steam on the water. It’s getting me excited for my favorite season that’s coming up very shortly 👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Faroe Islands with @opensea. May be an image of nature and lake.

node.text:
Here’s a piece titled “Halcyon Harbor” that will be available for purchase as a 1/1 NFT on @opensea as part of my Colors of the World Collection available this Wednesday, September 1st.

This collection encapsulates my travels, feelings, and experiences. It is composed of 48 unique images that are all 1/1, taken over the last five years. So excited! 😁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in California. May be an image of road, tree and nature.

node.text: This was a me off the crazier sunrises I’ve seen, as a huge inversion rolled in right before the sun came up. I shoot this at about 200mm, so pretty far away. This focal length usually fills in the frame quite well

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Hawaii with @jessicabertken. May be an image of one or more people, beach, body of water and nature.

node.text: Soaking it all in at one of the best beach views I’ve seen 🏝 These crystal clear waters were the perfect way to start the day 🤙🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Italian Dolomites with @antoniomiravete. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text: It would be a dream to visit here again. These incredibly jagged peaks make this my favorite mountain range. I can’t wait to visit again. I might have to make that happen sooner than I thought…

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Kauai with @jessicabertken. May be an image of nature and mountain.

node.text: Ridgeline dreams ✨ this must’ve been the best way to end a proper trip to the garden island. I can’t wait to visit again

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of mountain, sky and nature.

node.text: One of the best mountain views ever. It’s evenings like this that you’ll never forget

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Lake Tahoe. May be an image of nature and body of water.

node.text: This place has some of the most beautiful and perfect water you’ll ever see. Last summer I visited Lake Tahoe 3-4 times and had the time of my life. Wish I could’ve made it back this year

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of sky and nature.

node.text: Here’s a shot from a recent heli flight over Washington and the Cascade Mountains. We saw a hot air balloon floating over Rainier as we headed back to Seattle. Definitely got super lucky. Check out my story for the raw photo and video flying past the balloon. Forgive me for the quality 😂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Cascade Mountains. May be an image of mountain and nature.

node.text: Cabin at the very top of the world 👀 Insane to think that they actually built this lookout at the very top of a pinnacle. I can’t even imagine what the process was like

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by RYAN RESATKA in Wyoming. May be an image of nature and road.

node.text: Wyoming - definitely one of the wildest places out there 🤠
